Investor Presentation | Asia Pacific
China Equity Strategy: New Highs for the Market; What's Next?
MORGAN STANLEY ASIA LIMITED+

Morgan Stanley does and seeks to do business with companies covered in Morgan Stanley Research. As a result, investors should be aware that the firm may have a conflict of interest that could affect the objectivity of Morgan Stanley Research. Investors should consider Morgan Stanley Research as only a single factor in making their investment decision.
For analyst certification and other important disclosures, refer to the Disclosure Section, located at the end of this report.

\(+ =\) Analysts employed by non- U.S. affiliates are not registered with FINRA, may not be associated persons of the member and may not be subject to FINRA restrictions on communications with a subject company, public appearances and trading securities held by a research analyst account.

Source: Morgan Stanley Research. Note: Tick indicates our view on the factor is improving, while \(\times\) indicates the factor is deteriorating, and \(\times \times\) indicates a greater level of deterioration.
- MSCI China's ROE effectively toughed in 2024 and is likely to catch up with MSCI EM's by the end of 2026, based on the following:
- Diligent corporate self-help and active shareholder enhancement activities;- Offshore Chinese universe over time becoming less influenced by macro conditions and deflation.
- MSCI China wrapping up a 13-quarter run of earnings estimate cuts, delivering in-line results for both 4Q24 and 1Q25, as well as the best quarterly pre-announcement since end of 2021;
- Regulatory shift from rectification to revitalization - more supportive for the private sector;
- China demonstrating its capability to persist with technology breakthroughs and remain/lead in AI competition, despite cost and equipment hurdles;
- Incremental top-down efforts to rebalance the economy through reigning in supplies and potentially stimulating demand -
- Anti-involution initiatives;- Consumption trade-in program and childcare subsidy
- US/China trade talks and other signs of geopolitical development;
- Execution of Anti-Involution initiatives;
- Sep/October policy events including NPC Standing Committee Meeting, and the 4th Plenary

China has large and integrated supply chain to drive efficiency gains and cost reductions.
China is the only economy that covers all traditional and emerging manufacturing sectors.
China has been the key driver of decarbonization globally.
Leverage automation and digital technology to facilitate cost reduction and process refinement.
China has a large talent pool to support broad exploration of different technological routes across various industries.

series.name: Top-Right Quadrant

series.name: Bottom-Left Quadrant
values: Deflation to persist into 2026 as reflation remains gradual; but exit from deflation would be durable.

series.name: Bottom-Right Quadrant
values: More robust and sustainable reflation to take hold as economic rebalancing speed up.
